body:
After #3363, we make a new function for each forked process. Such functions are of the form:
```
fork(syms, whatnot) {
 whatnot = syms->whatnot + 1;
 co_await
 sym->other = whatnot;
}
```
Even if `whatnot` is not live entering the fork, it's being passed as an argument, even though it should be local.

This requires dataflow analysis to tackle properly, to handle all possible branching.
